<br>
I think it can be done, but in general it won't be a &quot;newb&quot; guild.  Most of the people you pick up will have some sort of experience raiding from prior guilds, etc so the true newness of it all won't necessarily be there.<br>
<br>
As for me, it is all new to me and I'm having a blast.  I've only been playing since August '02 and I haven't yet been hit by the &quot;you group can't do this&quot; mentality so I'm pretty much up for anything.  Of course being a mage [/flex] and knowing that we can do the impossible helps.  =p<br>
<br>
Case in point, we went to the hole and nearly succeeded in killing the mob Kirn for the shaman epic.  We did this without crowd control and a 53 ranger pulling.  Haha.  Many close calls but it was intense and lots of fun.  We could have pulled it off too, but the last mob we needed clear before Kirn brought 5 friends with it, including a named.  Good times.<br>
<br>
Casala, lvl 56 Conjurer of Saryn <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nightfog>Nightfog</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 374<br> <font color=#333333>(2/21/03 10:42:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=448.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.familjenguild.com/images/members/thumb_amel.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Can a successful RAID guild be created in today's EQ?</span><hr size=1> Just get everyone signed in on the same mission statement.<br>
<br>
Open recruiting is dangerous as you need to get people that have the same goal and like the method the guild will use to reach that goal.<br>
<br>
You have your casual game and your extreme gamer and you need to keep both entertained.<br>
<br>
The extreme gamers are not likely to enjoy 4 exp days and 2 raid days and the casual gamer needs to understand that the extreme gamers will by nature get better equipment faster than the casual gamer.<br>
<br>
Also the leadership needs to be confident and in control.  It's not easy work.<br>
<br>
