I'm in an up-and-coming guild on Kane Bayle. It's a server less than a year old, so the guild situation is still developing.  I'm in a guild that is about 6 months old, and moving right along. <br>
<br>
I think there will be some very strong guilds being formed on the newer servers, and some on the older servers. Of course, on old servers most tough guilds will be formed from the remnants of previous guilds, so those guilds aren't exactly working their way up from scratch.<br>
<br>
It seems to me that EQ continually becomes more oriented around raids, as opposed to soloing/grouping, and PoP is no exception.  I personally find the emphasis on uber-guild raiding pretty lame, but Verant is still designing content centered around it.  I assume lots of people support this (at least the small percentage of hyper-vocal EQ raid fiends do), and I don't expect change, since Verant can't undo all the content they have already created. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=swagman@themagicianstower>swagman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#333333>(2/22/03 2:29:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=448.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   raiding Guild</span><hr size=1> It can be done. A small elite quild of 60 plus power gamers maybe 25-30 people strong. Think of the possibilities. Fill the quild with solid people that you have met in your journies. Some may just have had it with the guild there in, others may just want a fresh look. It can be done, maintained, and very rewarding. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eloinapyromancer>Eloina Pyromancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 450<br> <font color=#333333>(2/22/03 3:54:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=448.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: raiding Guild</span><hr size=1> We saw some people do it on Torv over the last 6 months.  From creation the guild recruited about 60+ characters with an average level around 60 or so.  It quickly ramped itself through the Kunark and Velious encounters, and was working on the high-end Luclin content when leadership issues arose, it stalled, and finally imploded.<br>
<br>
So, I think it's possible to create such a guild.  As always, keeping it together is a challenge. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shazar23>Shazar23</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 504<br> <font color=#333333>(2/22/03 6:06:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=448.topic&index=16>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: raiding Guild</span><hr size=1> It all depends on the players in the guild.  If they can work as a team on common goals, sure, they can make it.  It just takes time and a lot of effort.<br>
<br>
A guild may become an uberguild but there's no guarantee it will remain one.  Squabbles and infighting can bring any guild down and the ubers are certainly not immune.<br>
<br>
Leadership is key.  There are plenty of competent players, but folks who can lead and motivate dozens of people into action are rare.   <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=363562" target="top">Shazar Oom</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->62 Arch Mage<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqheroes.com" target="top">Heroes</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> </div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=datalore>Datalore </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 214<br> <font color=#333333>(2/23/03 7:51:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=448.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: raiding Guild</span><hr size=1> It's not impossible, but very hard to pull off. Three key things you'd need to crack -<br>
<br>
* Common goals - start from the beginning with a vision, and ensure all new members are also motivated by the same vision; the guild I helped build on the Rathe (www.tindilosi.com) went from an unknown guild to a VT-enabled guild that will soon defeat Rallos Zek the Warlord with the vision &quot;we want to kill every mob and overcome every challenge in the game&quot;<br>
<br>
* Loyalty - you need to figure out a way to keep members inside the game and inside the guild. Every skilled and equipped member you lose will set you back.<br>
<br>
* Patience - the path will be a long one. It may be too late in EQ's lifecycle to build a new uberguild from scratch.<br>
<br>
A good leadership team would achieve all of the above requirements by<br>
<br>
- creating and maintaining a fair loot award system<br>
- spending time talking with members and addressing their concerns<br>
- building camaraderie, friendship and bonds throughout the guild, you will need them to navigate life-and-death events in your guild's history<br>
- being proactive; work out ways to get things done faster, better, easier; figure out how to get your members get keys, flags, spells, AA, epics, etc.<br>
- work hard to retain members, but be prepared to deal with inevitable member turnover<br>
<br>
